   29\%), and porosity (by 8\%). From principal component analysis, three
   soil properties-soil organic carbon (SOC), porosity, and P
   availability-were selected as key indicators suitable for the evaluation
   of the effects of cultivation on soils. Establishment of C. caeruleum
