   ranged from 30.2+/-1.8 (75 year plot) to 47.5+/-2.1 g C kg(-1) soil (5
   year plot), while microbial biomass carbon content varied from
   340.2+/-5.9 (75 year plot) to 371.2+/-10.2 mg C kg(-1) soil (5 year
   plot). Among the three agricultural treatments, only the 75 year one
   resulted in a significant decline in total amounts of water-stable
   aggregates (70.8+/-8.2\%) and clay content (26.9+/-1.0\%), compared to
   those parameters in the fallow land (90.1+/-9.4\% and 30.5+/-1.2\%,
   respectively). Distribution of the minimum values of differential
   entropy of water vapour adsorption in the soil also showed that the 75
   year agricultural management unfavourably affected the thermodynamic
