   Though the standard L soil should be used for reproducibility and
   comparison means, other natural soils should be added to the assessment
   of chemicals, for sake of ecological relevance. Both herbicides induced
   avoidance behaviour on E. andrei, albeit stronger effects were denoted
   by penoxsulam and its respective formulated product, Viper. Overall,
   avoidance tests provided a sensitive, valuable and feasible response
   either to compare the habitat function of different standard and
   agricultural natural soils or to test the effect of herbicides.
   An effort should be made to enlarge the terrestrial ecotoxicological
